My Introduction!

Hello, my name is Tess! I currently live in Dayton, OH. However, I have moved around a lot in my life. I have lived in Iowa, Minnesota, South Dakota, North Carolina, and now Ohio!

Academic Background

Professional Background

With my previous degree in Biology I originally wanted to enter the Developmental Biology field. I worked at Cincinnati Childrens in the Fetal Department, studing the development of the fetal immune system and their potential ability to receive a stem cell transplant in utero. I then became a Lab Manager in the Experimental Hematology and Cancer Biology Department for Dr.Leighton Grimes. We studied how the biological processes of cell development goes wrong. I became very interested in the data analysis our colaborators were doing! That is why I enrolled in the Business Analytics program at University of Cincinnati.
